# Server Ktor Conventions

## Required Orchestration
- For substantive work under `server/**`, first invoke `.cursor/skills/server-ktor-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.
- If the server change also affects shared code under `common/**`, invoke `.cursor/skills/common-module-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.
- Before completion, invoke `.cursor/skills/repo-verification-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.

## Application structure
- Keep server bootstrap in `Application.kt` or similarly focused entry files.
- Keep Ktor `Application.module()` wiring readable and small.
- Prefer extracting route or plugin setup when `module()` starts accumulating unrelated concerns.

## Ktor testing
- Prefer `testApplication { ... }` for server tests.
- Verify HTTP status and response body behavior explicitly.
- Keep tests in `server/src/test/kotlin`.

## Boundaries
- Do not move feature-specific client/UI logic into `server/`.
- If shared abstractions are needed by both server and KMP clients, place them deliberately in `common/**` and validate boundaries through the common-module orchestrator.
